Charles Robert BAYLESS v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5227. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 12, 1955. No appearance for appellant. William C. Farmer, U. S. Atty., and Milton P. Beach, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and HUXMAN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee, for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
